article.headline: Northern Arizona 78, Montana State 72
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Tyrone Bazy scored 16 points, Ruben Boykin Jr. had 14 points and 10 rebounds, and Northern Arizona beat Montana State 78-72 on Saturday night to stay unbeaten in Big Sky Conference play. Boykin had 12 points in the second half, when the Lumberjacks (14-6, 6-0) managed to hold the lead without ever getting more than seven points ahead. Kelly Golob scored 12 points, and Josh Wilson and Kyle Landry finished with 10 points each. Ja'Ron Jefferson was 4-of-6 on 3-pointers and had 16 points to lead Montana State (10-9, 3-2). Marvin Moss added 14 points and 10 rebounds and Ted Morris went 6-for-6 from the field and finished with 12 points. The Lumberjacks trailed 33-29 with 2:45 left in the first half, but finished the half with a 9-0 run. The Bobcats stayed close, and cut the lead to 75-72 with under a minute left on a 3-pointer by Jefferson. But Northern Arizona made 3-of-4 free throws to finish.
